NeuroWell Conversational Agent: A Multi-Stage AI Framework for Personalized Student Mental Health Support (NeuroWell-CA)

1DR. LALITHA KUMARA GADDALA, 2CHINTHALAPATI SRI VENKATA SAI SUBRAHMANYAM, 3 AAKASH KODALI, 4 ABDUL AZEEZ, 5ABDUL JABBAR

1Sr. Assistant Professor, 2345Student Scholars Department of CSE, 
Prasad V Potluri Siddhartha Institute of Technology, Andhra Pradesh, INDIA

E-mail: subrahmanyam310308@gmail.com


 
Abstract— In recent years, the prevalence of depression and anxiety has increased significantly, particularly among students, leading to reduced productivity and the adoption of unhealthy coping mechanisms. Factors such as academic pressure, societal expectations, inadequate emotional guidance, and limited psychological awareness contribute to this growing mental health concern. To address this issue, this project proposes a multi-stage AI-based mental health support system designed to assess psychological well-being and provide personalized assistance.
The proposed system consists of three core stages. The first stage involves a structured psychological assessment using standardized questionnaires to evaluate an individual’s emotional state, behavioural tendencies, and social interactions. These assessment results are utilized to generate a personalized psychological profile using a secure, pre-trained Large Language Model (LLM). The second stage introduces a personalized AI assistant that functions as a supportive companion, offering emotionally responsive conversations, stress management guidance, and decision-making support tailored to the user’s psychological profile. The final stage incorporates interactive stress-relief and entertainment-based activities aimed at reducing mental fatigue and promoting emotional well-being.
This system is primarily targeted toward students, a demographic particularly vulnerable to mental stress due to academic and societal pressures. By integrating psychological assessment, personalized AI interaction, and stress-relief engagement, the proposed solution aims to promote healthy coping strategies, enhance emotional resilience, and contribute to improved mental health outcomes.
Keywords—Artificial Intelligence & Machine Learning, Gemini, API, Flask 
