 Chai et al. (2001) analyze the role of natural language conversational interfaces in online sales, demonstrating that conversational agents significantly improve user engagement and task completion. Although focused on e-commerce, the findings are transferable to healthcare chatbots, where conversational clarity and user trust are critical for effective interaction.
In [9], Advancing language-specific healthcare solutions, Polignano et al. (2020) introduce HealthAssistantBot, a personal health assistant designed for the Italian language. Their system integrates natural language processing with health knowledge bases to deliver personalized responses. The study confirms that culturally and linguistically adapted chatbots enhance user satisfaction and effectiveness in healthcare contexts. 
In [10], Rauv (2023) explores the broader impact of technology in healthcare, identifying benefits such as improved efficiency, patient-centered care, and enhanced data-driven decision-making. The study also cautions against challenges related to data privacy, ethical responsibility, and system reliability, which are particularly critical in mental health applications.
  
III. METHODOLOGY

The proposed system follows a muilty-staged structured system, designed for psychological well-being and provide personalized mental health Assistant using artificial intelligence. The overall architecture is divided into three steps: psychological assessment, personalized AI assistance, and stress-relief entertainment engagement.
1. Psychological Assessment Phase
In this stage it focuses on assessing the psychology of the individual by the series of questions asked in test format these questions will be in multiple answers, text input these questions will determine the view of individual toward the society, his wisdom on the situation’s emotional stability.
The responses obtained from the assessment are pre-processed and encoded into structured formats suitable for machine learning models. This processed data is then used to generate an individualized psychological profile. To ensure data security and user privacy, all assessment data is encrypted before storage and further processing.
2. Personalized AI Assistant Phase
In the second phase, a pre-trained Large Language Model (LLM) is employed to generate a personalized AI assistant based on the user’s psychological profile. The LLM is fine-tuned or contextually adapted using the assessment results to align its conversational behavior, tone, and support strategies with the individual’s emotional needs and personality traits.
The AI assistant engages users through natural language interactions, providing emotional support, stress management techniques, motivational guidance, and decision-support suggestions. It actively participates in conversations, monitors emotional cues, and encourages healthy coping behaviors. This phase emphasizes empathetic communication, personalization, and continuous adaptation based on user interactions while maintaining strict privacy and security protocols.
3. Stress-Relief and Engagement Phase
The final phase integrates interactive entertainment and stress-relief activities designed to promote relaxation and emotional balance. These activities include simple games, mindfulness exercises, and engagement-based modules that help users divert negative thoughts and reduce mental fatigue. The selection of activities is personalized based on the user’s psychological profile and interaction history.
This phase acts as a supplementary support mechanism, reinforcing positive emotional states and providing a healthy outlet for stress. User engagement metrics are monitored to refine activity recommendations and improve effectiveness over time.
                                    
